File: Michael Schumacher poses with the Mercedes team in the pits on November 25, 2012 at the Interlagos speedway in Sao Paulo, Brazil. JOHANNESBURG - Michael Schumacher is reportedly “conscious” after undergoing stem-cell treatment in Paris. According to Neurology expert, Matilde Leonardi, Schumacher may be in a state of minimum consciousness, which will allow him to turn his head and show some emotion. READ: Leclerc triggers Ferrari frenzy with Italian GP win The seven-time world champion has not been seen in public since hitting his head in a skiing accident in 2013. Schumacher's family has been rather secretive about the 50-year-old’s condition.